<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03023c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03023c">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03023c"> 23(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Scot (Irish) / <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">chu</span></span> ecclesia Scotorum, nay Romanorum / (SP)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Irish Church had been careful to preserve carefully the tradition of the faith that had been brought to her by St. Patrick from Rome, the centre of Christendom, and she kept ever before her his maxim: &ldquo;O <mark>Church of the Scots</mark> &mdash; <mark>nay of the Romans</mark> &mdash; as ye are Christians, be ye also Romans.&rdquo; <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 57-8</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
